All Classes and Interfaces

Classes
Class
Description
AirBlock
Air block in the planet's composition, has information regarding the block and controls what happens on QTE events
Block
The block superclass that makes the composition of the planet in the bottom left of the game
Creature
Creates planets and animals that exist in the game which will grow in population or go extinct
Driver
The driver of the game, runs the code
GamePanel
This panel is visible when the game has started
IceBlock
The Ice block in the planet's composition.
LavaBlock
The Lava block in the planet's composition.
LeaderboardPanel
Controls the data and the graphics of the leaderboard page
LeaderboardPanel.Player
Subclass that creates a player that has a score and a name
LightsGame
Lights minigame that requires you to click on lights to turn them off
MazeGame
The maze minigame which requires you to recycle trash
MenuPanel
The menu panel which shows the main menu with options and handles menu operations
Minigame
Minigame superclass that launches when smog QTEs are clicked
MinigameHandler
A minigame handler that starts a new thread to play the minigame
Objective
Objective in the game with a prompt and description
ObjectivePanel
Display and handles objectives to complete in the game
Planet
Planet containing the blocks and creatures and has other game information such as temp and score
ProtestGame
The protest minigame initiated when smog qte is clicked on, space spammer
QTEPanel
JPanel that controls the QTE popups
RockBlock
Rock block in the planet's composition

Smog block in the planet's composition

Common utilities used around the game

Water block in the planet's composition

The window containing the game
